ard, but this was balanced by the sweet potato and carrot mash I served it with. I would probably go for a sweeter alternative next time, but tasty overall.</div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrapper-765546"><a id="comment-765546"></a><article class="comment"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"> <span class="comment__author-picture--no-login"></span></div><div class="comment__author-name"> <span class="username">mummyellie</span></div><div class="comment__date"> 13th May, 2014</div> </header><div class="comment__rating-and-report-wrapper"><div class="comment__rating"><div class="rate-widget rate-widget-fivestar clear-block rate-processed"><div class="fivestar-bbcgoodfood"><div class="clearfix fivestar-widget-static fivestar-widget-static-vote fivestar-widget-static-5"><div class="star star-1 star-odd star-first"><span class="on">5.05</span></div><div class="star star-2 star-even"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-3 star-odd"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-4 star-even"><span class="on"></span></div><div class="star star-5 star-odd star-last"><span class="on"></span></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="comment__text"><div class="field field-name-comment-body field-type-text-long field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even">Still in love with this recipe, however recently I've started cutting up the bacon/gammon, using golden syrup instead of marmalade and cooking the sauce down till i'ts very sticky then serving on top of a jacket potato. It's one of my favourite meals.</div></div></div></div> </article></div></div><div><div id="comment-wrapper-732776"><a id="comment-732776"></a><article class="comment"> <header class="comment__header"><div class="comment__author-picture"> <span class="comment__author-picture--no-login"></span></div><div class="comment__author-name"> <span class="username">collyg53</span></div><div class="co